{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb6a4d5f8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–121"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"300ff–121"},"text":"§ 300ff–121.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Minority AIDS initiative","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a4d5f9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–121/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For the purpose of carrying out activities under this section to evaluate and address the disproportionate impact of HIV/AIDS on, and the disparities in access, treatment, care, and outcomes for, racial and ethnic minorities (including African Americans, Alaska Natives, Latinos, American Indians, Asian Americans, Native Hawaiians, and Pacific Islanders), there are authorized to be appropriated $131,200,000 for fiscal year 2007, $135,100,000 for fiscal year 2008, $139,100,000 for fiscal year 2009, $146,055,000 for fiscal year 2010, $153,358,000 for fiscal year 2011, $161,026,000 for fiscal year 2012, and $169,077,000 for fiscal year 2013. The Secretary shall develop a formula for the awarding of grants under subsections (b)(1)(A) and (b)(1)(B) that ensures that funding is provided based on the distribution of populations disproportionately impacted by HIV/AIDS.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a4d5fa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–121/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Certain activities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb6a4d5fb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5